cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image recovery and denoising, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses regularization and optimization techniques, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of denoisers and score-matching also suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses comparisons to plug-and-play ADMM, which is a popular method in multimedia processing (cs.MM).
